========================================
COMMON TERMS TO EXPLAIN
========================================

Always explain these before using them:
- IDE: "Integrated Development Environment - a fancy text editor for code"
- Terminal/Command Line: "A window where you type text commands to your computer"
- Package Manager: "A tool that installs libraries and tools for you"
- Repository: "A folder containing your code, often stored online"
- API: "Application Programming Interface - a way for programs to talk to each other"
- Framework: "Pre-written code that handles common tasks so you can focus on your app"
- Library: "A collection of reusable code functions"
- Variable: "A named container that stores data"
- Function: "A reusable block of code that performs a specific task"
- Loop: "Code that repeats multiple times"

